# .dockerignore for `podman build -f deploy/podman/Dockerfile.server .`
# (build context root = repo root). Trim heavy / sensitive things; keep
# everything the multi-stage builder actually needs.
#
# Explicitly KEPT (do not add patterns that match these):
#   - internal/webui/static/*            (committed minified JS/CSS bundles)
#   - internal/webui/templates/*_templ.go (committed templ-generated Go)
#   - .git/                              (so go build records VCS revision)

# --- IDE / editor / OS noise -----------------------------------------------
.claude/
.idea/
.vscode/
.DS_Store

# --- Local Go build output -------------------------------------------------
# `make build` drops binaries here; useless inside the image and would
# bloat the build context.
bin/
dist/
/flow
/flow-server
/flow-mcp

# --- Local dev secrets / state ---------------------------------------------
# Cookie keys generated by scripts/run-flow-server.sh — must never end up
# in the image.
.flow-cookie-keys
deploy/podman/.env
*.db
*.db-shm
*.db-wal

# --- Test + coverage artifacts ---------------------------------------------
coverage.out
coverage.html
*.test
*.out

# --- npm caches (we copy lockfiles + run `npm ci` inside the builder) ------
**/node_modules/

# --- Generated docs / planning artefacts -----------------------------------
# Memory-bank + planning files Claude maintains locally — never committed,
# but a stale checkout might still carry them. Exclude defensively.
CLAUDE.md
CLAUDE-*.md
GEMINI.md
GEMINI-*.md

# --- Git internals we don't need inside the image build context ------------
# .git is kept (see header) so `go build` can stamp VCS info. Strip the
# obvious heavy subtrees that don't affect VCS metadata.
.git/hooks/
.github/
